    "Near a stationary point there is no linear dependence on θθ * and the quadratic terms are given by the Hessian (47) matrix.",
    "We can assume, without loss of generality, that the Hessian is diagonal.",
    "Let us introduce a, b = 1κ ± γ μ= 1/(ab) (93)",
    "and then μ will be the scalar magnification.",
    "In terms of these we have The term here is known as the Morse phase."
